---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />

		<main>
			<h1>Peak Rock Communication Services</h1>

			<p>
				My name is Alister, and I am a vanlifer, with 15 years of experience in the telecommunications and networking world. Due to my lifestyle, I am uniquely placed to reach all areas of the UK and Europe  to assist my customers with overhauling and renewing their network infrastructure. <br />
				I provide new installation and refurbishment of internet networks.
			</p>

			<section id="services" class="offerings">
				<div class="section-header">
					<h2>What I Do</h2>
					<button id="detailToggle" class="detail-toggle" type="button">Detailed mode</button>
				</div>

				<details>
					<summary>Customised Network Solutions</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Tailored network solutions for homes, businesses and unusual environments, designed around your actual needs rather than off-the-shelf solutions.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Every environment is unique, from farms to factories, houses to office blocks. I tailor solutions based on customers individual and unique needs.
						<br />
						I can optimise and provide solutions for internet failovers, automatically switching to a secondary service if the main one goes down, or ensure more important devices are prioritised when the network is being used to it's maximum bandwidth. I still think it's all magic, but I know most of the tricks.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Existing Network Testing and Auditing</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Testing, auditing and reviewing existing infrastructure so you can understand what is in place, what has changed over time, where problems are likely to arise and how to deal with them.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Whatever infrastructure and documentation is in place things grow and get added over time, stuff changes and that can lead to problems. 
						<br />
						Testing and auditing existing infrastructure is a part of every survey, including documentation, leaving you with a product you can trust to be reliable long term-7uuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuu
						.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Problem Solving</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Bespoke fault finding and infrastructure planning aimed at solving the root cause of network issues rather than applying temporary fixes.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Whatever the problem, there is a solution. I offer a bespoke service to engineer your network so that problems are considered in advance, ensuring reliability post installation.
						<br /> 
						I can't offer a quick fix 24-7 call out service for major breakdowns, as much as I'd love to - If that's you right now, there are usually local services who can give a quicker patch than me.
						<br /> 
						 I offer a long term solution and support by utilising a process of surveying and implementing the required standards for a solid infrastructure.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>CCTV</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Wired CCTV infrastructure planned and installed with proper cabling standards for reliability, clarity and long-term maintainability.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Wired CCTV systems benefit from the highest standard of cabling. Errors happen when renewing a system and utilising existing cabling (unless it's well structured), this compounds over time. In most cases I recommend a proper structured cabling solution, because it provides the most reliability and longevity.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Retail / POS</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Practical network and cabling solutions for card machines, tills and retail systems so everyday trading is not disrupted by avoidable faults.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						I've lost count of the number of shops I've helped out whilst popping in to by milk because the card machine is down. POS cabling is fundamentally simple, but often poorly implemented.
						<br / > 
						I offer solutions to retail, takeaway and restaurant businesses of all types sizes, to eliminate the normal problems that you'll know about if you're reading this. The solution is normally ensuring easy access to power, usb, and ethernet sockets. Judicious labelling, and instructional documents for staff members to quickly troubleshoot issues and upgrade equipment.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>121 Service</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Direct one-to-one service from survey through to implementation, I'm not restricted by management or sales channels, and take pride in providing the best value for my services.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						I can work with you to design, build and implement systems for you and your exact needs, not by a company policy and not by affiliate requirements. Should you choose to utilise my services, there's no company red tape or need to escalate to the boss, you will only ever need to deal with me.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>WiFi Solutions</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						WiFi design and improvement for homes, hospitality, rural sites and many more environments where plug-and-play kit does not deliver what is needed.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Whether you live in a castle or a flat, maintain an Airbnb, glamping site, or a farm, WiFi is one of those things we all want to just work - but seemingly never meets expectations. I have experience in everything from stadiums and large caravan parks down to bedsits in very crowded environment. The key is understanding the network requirement, not always relying on plug and play solutions.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Structured Cabling</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						High-quality structured cabling designed to proper standards, making your infrastructure easier to use, maintain and expand in future.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						I attained CCNI (certified network cable installer) and an NVQ Level 3 in Network Infrastructure / Cabling in 2018. Since then I have worked in some of the biggest networked buildings in the world (ask me about it). Ultimately, those wires that carry the internet about aren't just a jungle, space ship wiring or rat's nest, nor should they be. There are no regulations - and that leads to confusion, but there are meticulous standards. When they're followed, these systems become very easy to understand for anyone who has to maintain or use them. I can install the highest quality ethernet infrastructure in your home or business, and provide documentation and instruction to make sure you get the best out of it.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>First Fix Consultancy</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Planning network infrastructure at the right stage of a build, so connectivity is considered before the works are finished and the options are limited.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						All too often people consider the network only after they've completed the build. The plaster is on, the painter is in, all the plug sockets are right where they're wanted, but the TV doesn't work in the annex, and the office doesn't have any connectivity at all. 
						<br / >
						First Fix, I can provide a plan that can be implemented by myself, your own builder, or electrician. With all the considerations that your project deserves.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Final Fix and Implementation</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Final-stage installation, termination, testing and bring-up work to make sure the finished system is live, labelled and working as intended.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Final fix and implementation ensures everything is completed, tested, labelled and working as expected before handover. This includes termination, validation, and making sure the system is reliable in real use.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>PBX / Phone Systems</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Practical phone system design and setup for homes, offices and small business sites, whether replacing older systems or starting fresh.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Design and setup of practical phone systems suited to your environment, whether upgrading or starting fresh.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Guest WiFi Networks</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Guest WiFi designed to be easy for visitors to use while staying properly separated from the main network.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Simple and secure guest access solutions that don’t compromise your main network.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Internet Failover & Backup Connectivity</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Backup connectivity planning so a broadband failure does not stop the whole site from working.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Backup connectivity solutions to keep your network online when your main connection fails.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Starlink & 4G/5G Installations</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Alternative internet solutions for rural, mobile or difficult locations where fixed-line services are limited or unreliable.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Alternative connectivity setups for rural, mobile, or hard-to-reach locations.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Outbuilding & Multi-Building Connectivity</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Reliable connections between houses, annexes, offices, barns, workshops and other external buildings.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Reliable connections between buildings, annexes, workshops and external spaces.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Smart Devices & IoT Networking</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Network setups that properly support smart devices and connected systems without turning the whole environment into a management headache.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Network setups that properly support smart devices and growing connected environments.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Remote Access & Monitoring Setup</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Sensible remote access and monitoring options so systems are easier to support, understand and maintain.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Secure remote access and visibility into your network for easier management and support.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Hospitality & Airbnb Networking</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Network design for guest-facing environments where reliability, simplicity and repeatable performance matter.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Network design suited for guest environments where reliability and simplicity matter.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Network Documentation & Handover</summary>
					<p class="summary concise">
						Clear documentation, labelling and handover information so you are not left guessing how your own infrastructure works.
					</p>
					<p class="summary detailed">
						Clear documentation so your system is understandable, maintainable, and future-proof.
					</p>
				</details>
			</section>
		</main>

		<Footer />

		<script>
			const toggleButton = document.getElementById('detailToggle');
			const body = document.body;

			toggleButton?.addEventListener('click', () => {
				const isDetailed = body.classList.toggle('detailed-mode');
				toggleButton.textContent = isDetailed ? 'Short mode' : 'Ramble Mode';
			});
		</script>
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	main {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 100%;
		padding: 1.5rem 2rem 5rem;
		text-align: center;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: 4rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		line-height: 1.05;
	}

	p {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		max-width: 900px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.offerings {
		max-width: 950px;
		margin: 2.5rem auto 0;
		text-align: left;
	}

	.section-header {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
	}

	.offerings h2 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 2rem;
		text-align: left;
	}

	.detail-toggle {
		padding: 0.6rem 0.9rem;
		border: 1px solid #ccc;
		border-radius: 6px;
		background: white;
		cursor: pointer;
		font: inherit;
	}

	.offerings details {
		border: 1px solid #ccc;
		border-radius: 6px;
		background: white;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.offerings summary {
		cursor: pointer;
		padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
		font-size: 1rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.3;
	}

	.offerings summary::after {
		content: "+";
		float: right;
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		line-height: 1;
	}

	.offerings details[open] summary::after {
		content: "−";
	}

	.summary {
		margin: 0;
		padding: 0 1rem 0.95rem;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		line-height: 1.5;
		text-align: left;
		max-width: none;
	}

	.detailed {
		display: none;
	}

	body.detailed-mode .concise {
		display: none;
	}

	body.detailed-mode .detailed {
		display: block;
	}

	@media (max-width: 700px) {
		.section-header {
			flex-direction: column;
			align-items: stretch;
		}

		.offerings h2 {
			text-align: center;
		}
	}
</style>